      <div xml:id="NA380-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu pāṇaṟkut (G1+2: pāṇaṉukkut) tōḻi vāyiṉ maṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante refused the door to the bard.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA380">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            neyyuṅ kuyyu māṭi maiyoṭu</l>
<l>            mācupaṭ ṭaṉṟē kaliṅkamun tōḷuṅ</l>
<l>            titalai meṉmulait tīmpāl piliṟṟap</l>
<l>            putalvaṟ pullip puṉiṟunā ṟummē</l>
<l>            vāliḻai makaḷir cērit tōṉṟun</l>
<l>            tērōṟ kottaṉe mallē mataṉāṟ</l>
<l>            poṉpurai narampi ṉiṉkuraṟ cīṟiyā</l>
<l>            <seg>ḻeḻāal vallai yāyiṉun toḻāal</seg> <seg>puraiyō raṉṉa puraiyi ṉaṭpi</seg></l>
<l rend="indent4">            ṉiḷaiyōr kūmpukai maruḷvō rāṅkuk</l>
<l>            <seg>koṇṭucel pāṇaniṉ ṟaṇṭuṟai yūraṉaip</seg> <seg>kaṭṭāṅ kātu viṭṭāṅ kamaittu</seg></l>
<l>            pāṭumaṉaip pāṭal kūṭātu nīṭunilaip</l>
<l>            puraviyum pūṇilai muṉikuva</l>
<l>            virakila moḻiyalyām vēṭṭatil vaḻiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent4">            Fumbling with ghee and curry,</l>
<l>            [our] cloth is stained with dirt and [our] shoulders, embracing [our] son,</l>
<l rend="indent">                while sweet milk drizzles from [our] soft breasts with beauty spots,</l>
<l>            smell of the newly born.</l>
<l>            We are not equal to the one with a chariot</l>
<l rend="indent2">                that appears in the quarter of women with pure jewels. Therefore,</l>
<l rend="indent2">                though you are strong in raising the sweet-voiced small lute</l>
<l>            with gold-like strings, don’t worship [us].</l>
<l>            Take him [and] go, bard – the man from the village by the cool ghat,</l>
<l rend="indent2">                {controlling [him] as [one] abandoned, not enduring toddy,</l>
<l rend="indent3">                as those who are afraid of the closing hand of the young ones</l>
<l rend="indent4">                of defectless friendship, as [that of] great people.(?)}<note place="foot">This is no more than an attempt to make sense of the additional lines which are really tough (besides their being too many for the NA this might be a reason for their not being integrated).</note></l>
<l rend="indent">                In the prolonged state of not meeting singing in the singing house</l>
<l>            the horses too hate the state of being yoked.</l>
<l>            Don’t speak useless [words] in a way that is not wanted by us.</l>
    <lg type="alternate" sameAs="1b">
    <l>Bathing with oil and incense<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">neyyum kuuyum āṭi</term>: here we are faced with a very ambiguous phrase, and since the <term xml:lang="ta">āṭi</term> cannot be taken literal in any case, and we have parallels for both topoi (for a see KT 167, for b see NA 40), I for one see no way of coming to a decision.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
